In doing some cleanup in the dotnet fhir client noticed that the hl7.fhir.core-4.0.1.tgz package has included the search extension definitions. Is that correct?
https://hl7.org/fhir/questionnaireresponse-profiles.html#search
And specifically this one has a hasExtension('http://example.org') in it that doesn't exist. I checked at https://hl7.org/fhir/fhirpath.html and nothing, only hasValue()
These weren't in the old search-parameters.xml that was generated by the build tooling in the past.
@Grahame Grieve , is this right?
guess i overlooked that one. Want to make a task?
